# Clerk Billing & Subscriptions

All subscription and payment logic is handled by **Clerk Billing**. Never implement custom billing or payment logic.

## Plans & Features

**Plans:**
- `free_plan` — default free tier
- `pro` — paid plan

**Features:**
- `5_deck_limit` — user is capped at 5 decks
- `unlimited_decks` — user can create unlimited decks
- `ai_flash_card_generation` — user can generate cards with AI

## Checking Access (Server-Side)

Use `has()` from the `auth()` object to gate access in Server Components and Server Actions:

```ts
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'

const { has } = await auth()

// Check by plan
const isPro = has({ plan: 'pro' })

// Check by feature
const canUseAI = has({ feature: 'ai_flash_card_generation' })
const hasUnlimitedDecks = has({ feature: 'unlimited_decks' })
```

## Checking Access (Client-Side)

Use the `<Show>` component to conditionally render UI based on plan or feature:

```tsx
import { Show } from '@clerk/nextjs'

// Gate by feature
<Show
  when={{ feature: 'ai_flash_card_generation' }}
  fallback={<p>Upgrade to Pro to use AI generation.</p>}
>
  <AIGenerateButton />
</Show>

// Gate by plan
<Show
  when={{ plan: 'pro' }}
  fallback={<p>This feature is available on the Pro plan.</p>}
>
  <ProOnlyFeature />
</Show>
```

## Pricing Page

Use the `<PricingTable />` component for the pricing page:

```tsx
import { PricingTable } from '@clerk/nextjs'

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div style={{ maxWidth: '800px', margin: '0 auto', padding: '0 1rem' }}>
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Key Rules

- Never use custom payment or subscription logic — always use Clerk Billing
- Always use `has()` on the server and `<Show>` on the client for access control
- Gate deck creation behind `unlimited_decks` feature; enforce 5-deck cap for `5_deck_limit`
- Gate AI card generation behind `ai_flash_card_generation` feature
